    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA299-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟamākac colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said when HE was behind the fence.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA299">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uruke ḻiyāṉai yuṭaikoṇ ṭaṉṉa</l>
<l>            tatarpiṇi yaviḻnta tāḻai vāṉputar</l>
<l>            tayaṅkiruṅ kōṭa ṟūkkali ṉuṇṭātu</l>
<l>            vayaṅkiḻai makaḷir vaṇṭiṟ ṟāaṅ</l>
<l>            kāmar ciṟukuṭip pulampiṉu mavarkā </l>
<l>            ṇāmila mākuta laṟitu maṉṉō</l>
<l>            villeṟi pañci pōla malkutirai</l>
<l>            vaḷiporu vayaṅkupicir poṅku</l>
<l>            naḷikaṭaṟ cērppaṉoṭu nakāa vūṅkē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>See him, more than(?) the loneliness in [our] desirable small hamlet,</l>
<l rend="indent">where, as the bracelets of women with glowing jewels, the fine pollen</l>
<l rend="indent">spreads, when [the wind] lifts the glittering big white Malabar lilies</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the sky bushes by the Tāḻai trees that opened [their] dense fetters,</l>
<l rend="indent3">as garments worn by beautiful elephants,</l>
<l>– did we really know we would become nothing</l>
<l rend="indent">before we laughed with the man from the coast of the vast sea,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where glowing spray foams as the wind dashes at</l>
<l rend="indent3">the increasing waves, as cotton cleaned by an instrument<note place="foot">For a possible parallel of the cleaning of cotton with the help of an instrument see also NA 247.4 <term xml:lang="ta">eḵku uṟu pañciṟṟu</term>, where T.V.G. explains <term xml:lang="ta">eḵku</term> to be such an instrument (see, however, translation).</note>?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
